        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add model switch choices to /model",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add dynamic configured-model choices to the native `/model` command\n- enable the existing command argument menu path for `/model` so Slack can render model picks with its existing buttons/static_select/external_select machinery\n- keep bare `/model` status behavior when no configured model choices are available\n\n## Details\n\n`/think` already gets rich Slack command UI because its registry entry declares choices plus an argument menu. `/model` had a positional argument but no choices/menu metadata, so Slack had nothing to render before dispatching the command as plain text.\n\nThis change keeps the fix in the shared command registry: configured catalog entries become `provider/model` choices, and the existing `/model <provider/model>` setter handles the selected value. No Slack-specific command renderer changes are needed.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/commands-registry.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD`\n- `node --import tsx - <<'EOF' ...` registry smoke shown below\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Slack native slash-command UX for `/model` can now surface the existing command argument menu instead of requiring users to type a model id manually.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout in an isolated worktree from `origin/main`, running the actual command registry module after this patch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: ran this local terminal command against the patched checkout:\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx - <<'EOF'\nimport { findCommandByNativeName, resolveCommandArgMenu } from './src/auto-reply/commands-registry.ts';\nconst command = findCommandByNativeName('model');\nif (!command) throw new Error('missing /model command');\nconst menu = resolveCommandArgMenu({\n  command,\n  cfg: {\n    models: {\n      providers: {\n        openai: { models: [{ id: 'gpt-5.5', name: 'GPT-5.5' }] },\n        anthropic: { models: [{ id: 'claude-sonnet-4.6', name: 'Claude Sonnet 4.6' }] },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n});\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify({ arg: menu?.arg.name, choices: menu?.choices }, null, 2));\nEOF\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: terminal output from the patched OpenClaw registry smoke:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"arg\": \"model\",\n  \"choices\": [\n    {\n      \"value\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6\",\n      \"label\": \"anthropic/Claude Sonnet 4.6\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"value\": \"openai/gpt-5.5\",\n      \"label\": \"openai/GPT-5.5\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: `/model` now resolves a native command argument menu for configured model choices, using `provider/model` values that the existing `/model <provider/model>` setter dispatch path already accepts. Focused registry tests also passed 31/31.\n\nWhat was not tested: live Slack Block Kit interaction against a real Slack workspace. The Slack plugin path reused here is already covered by existing arg-menu render/dispatch tests; this PR adds the missing registry metadata that feeds that path.\n\n## Notes\n\nAI-assisted with human-requested agent workflow. The local commit helper hydrated ignored `node_modules` in the isolated worktree before committing; no tracked dependency or lockfile changes are included.\n",
